    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="169"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2004: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 11, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>388. Your 739, October 11, 10 a.m.<note n="24" xml:id="d169fn24">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>(1)</label>
                    <item>The Department desires a complete report at the earliest possible moment
                        regarding the bombing of Chinchow, to include as full an account as possible
                        of the incident, the number of casualties, the damage to property, etc. You
                        should in your discretion make what arrangements you consider most feasible
                        for a prompt execution. If it can be attained by immediately sending Hanson
                        and Salisbury to the spot, you should rush instructions for them to proceed
                        there and at the earliest possible moment to report. Otherwise someone else
                        should be sent.</item>
                    <label>(2)</label>
                    <item>Inform the Department of the present whereabouts of Hanson and Salisbury
                        and of the arrangements made by you to carry out the above.</item>
                    <label>(3)</label>
                    <item>The foregoing should be regarded as unusually urgent.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
